              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at ISAC-1",
                "facility at TRIUMF, Vancouver"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "CH2 target with thickness of 638 mu-g/cm2 located at",
                "the center of TIGRESS."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES",
                "SISD",
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two forward silicon telescopes were",
                "opimized to detect and identify deuterons. Thickened",
                "of dE detector was 40 mu-m, thickness of E detector",
                "varied according to experimental conditions between",
                "295 mu-m and 505 mu-m. This allowed for the detection",
                "and identification of deuterons with energies greater",
                "than 2 MeV and up to 14 MeV (17 MeV) ."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " TIGRESS gamma array consists of 12 HPGe",
                "detectors with eight high-purity germanium (HPGe)",
                "clovers at 90 deg and four (upstream of the target)",
                "at 135 deg with respect to the beam axis. Since",
                "high-energy gamma rays being detected, the TIGRESS",
                "array was configured in a high-efficiency mode and",
                "signals collected by each clover were read out in",
                "addback mode."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Coincidence between charged particle",
                "telescope and TIGRESS gamma ray array was required.",
                "Inverse kinematics was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The 11Be beam was produced by 479 MeV proton beam on",
                "Ta target and extracted using the TRIUMF Resonant",
                "Ionization Laser Ion Source. The beam was then",
                "post-accelerated to 9.93 MeV/A through the ISAC-I and",
                "ISAC-II accelerators and delivered to the TIGRESS",
                "beam line. The beam intensity was around 1E+5",
                "particles/sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
